3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bitget calculates FTM/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC based on the premium between perpetual and spot prices. The exchange uses a time-weighted average price mechanism over the final hour before settlement. Funding payments are automatically debited or credited to traders' accounts, with rates typically ranging from -0.1% to +0.1% during normal market conditions."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","FTM","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FTM/USDT presents compelling arbitrage potential due to Fantom's volatile funding dynamics and strong correlation with DeFi narrative cycles. The pair often experiences sustained funding rate imbalances during network upgrade announcements or ecosystem developments, creating extended arbitrage windows for strategic positioning."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FTM/USDT funding rates on Bitget have shown distinct seasonal patterns, with consistently positive rates during DeFi summer periods and network milestone releases. Historical data indicates funding rates spike above +0.2% during major Fantom ecosystem announcements, often sustaining elevated levels for 3-5 days. The pair exhibits lower volatility in funding rates compared to newer L1 tokens, making it suitable for longer-term carry strategies. Winter months typically see funding rates oscillate around the -0.05% to +0.05% range, providing stable but modest arbitrage returns."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Strategy"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bitget's fast listing policy and copy trading ecosystem create unique funding rate inefficiencies in FTM/USDT that experienced arbitrageurs can exploit. The exchange's growing user base often leads to momentum-driven positioning, resulting in funding rate premiums that persist longer than on more mature platforms. Cross-exchange arbitrage between Bitget and established venues like Binance frequently yields 10-20 basis points in additional alpha. Traders should monitor Fantom's total value locked (TVL) metrics and ecosystem announcements to anticipate funding rate direction changes."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations and Management"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FTM/USDT carries elevated smart contract risk due to Fantom's smaller validator set compared to Ethereum or Solana, potentially affecting funding rate stability during network stress. Bitget's shorter operational history introduces counterparty risk that must be factored into position sizing decisions. Liquidity gaps can occur during Asian trading hours, leading to wider spreads and potential slippage on larger arbitrage positions. The exchange's customer support inconsistency may complicate dispute resolution, making automated strategies and smaller position sizes advisable for risk management."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What are typical FTM/USDT funding rates on Bitget?","answer":"FTM/USDT funding rates on Bitget typically range from -0.1% to +0.1% during normal market conditions, settling every 8 hours. During high volatility or major Fantom announcements, rates can spike to ±0.3% or higher."},{"question":"How does Bitget's FTM funding compare to other exchanges?","answer":"Bitget often shows slightly higher funding rate premiums than established exchanges due to its growing retail user base and copy trading features. This creates arbitrage opportunities but requires monitoring for sudden liquidity changes."},{"question":"What's the minimum position size for FTM funding arbitrage?","answer":"Bitget allows minimum FTM perpetual positions of $10 USDT equivalent, but profitable funding arbitrage typically requires positions of $1,000+ to overcome transaction costs. The exchange's 0.02%/0.06% fee structure makes smaller positions less economical."},{"question":"Can I automate FTM funding rate strategies on Bitget?","answer":"Bitget provides REST and WebSocket APIs for automated trading, supporting funding rate data collection and position management. However, API rate limits and the exchange's newer infrastructure may require more robust error handling compared to established venues."}]}]
